Local Functions (/std/inheritables/living.c)

void use_skill(string skill, int val);

This call will both train the skill and the skill's improvement value.  By using this call it is possible to easilly rebalance all skill training by only ever having to edit this function and not the dozens of spells and skills, special items and so on in the game.  IE: use this function, do not use add_skill_points() and set_skill_adjustment() when skills are in use.

See also: set_skill_adjustment(), set_skills(), set_skill(), query_skills(), query_skill_level(), query_skill_adjustment(), query_base_skill(), set_skill_bonus(), add_skill_bonus(), query_skill_bonus(), add_skill_points(), add_skill_adj_points()

